    <question>
        <prompt>Modern liberalism in the 1920s emphasized:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Business deregulation</option>
            <option letter="b">Civil liberties and individual rights</option>
            <option letter="c">Conservative economic policies</option>
            <option letter="d">Immigration restrictions</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Modern liberalism in the 1920s emphasized the protection of civil liberties and individual rights, marking a shift from Progressive Era reforms. Organizations like the ACLU exemplified this new liberalism by defending free speech, religious freedom, and minority rights. This transformation laid the groundwork for New Deal liberalism that would emerge in the 1930s, combining economic reform with civil rights protection.</explanation>
